# Trivy suppressions for the blocking dependency scan (.github/workflows/security.yml).
#
# This file is INTENTIONALLY EMPTY. As of the Spring Boot 4.0.7 upgrade the backend and
# frontend scan clean at 0 HIGH/CRITICAL, so nothing is suppressed and the gate blocks on
# every HIGH/CRITICAL finding.
#
# Only add an entry when a HIGH/CRITICAL vulnerability has NO available fix yet and is
# genuinely not exploitable in our usage. Each entry MUST carry a justification and a review
# date, e.g.:
#
#   # CVE-2026-XXXXX — transitive via <lib>; no fix released; not reachable because <reason>.
#   # Added 2026-07-18 by <who>. Re-check by 2026-08-18.
#   CVE-2026-XXXXX
#
# Never add an entry just to make CI green. A suppression is a tracked, dated exception —
# not a way to weaken the gate.
